From Ron Phillips Subject Randy Weaver Trail Day This was posted to the firearms politics mailing Hi Folks Thursday April marked Day of the This day marked the first testimony of the Deputy Marshal Larry Cooper took the stand for the The short version is that his testimony was consistent with the opening statements for the Cooper testified that he had arrived in Spokane Washington on August to participate in a surveillance operation with five other deputies near the Weaver The team was using night vision equipment for surveillance and split up into two teams of three The six later met at an observation point above the After this deputies Cooper William Degan and Arthur Roderick began a descent to scout further possible surveillance Cooper told the court that Roderick threw two large rocks into a gully to see whether the Weaver family dogs would Striker the Weaver's yellow lab started toward them barking Roderick led the three in a run from the They ran through some dense woods into an open area called the fern field with the dog in By this time Kevin Harris and Samuel Weaver had joined the The surveillance team had reached a Y in the road Cooper decided that they should take cover in the woods because otherwise they would be an easy target and might be shot in the As Degan reached the Y he spotted Randy Weaver coming down the road from the cabin Weaver was startled but did not At this moment Striker reached Degan and Cooper had to fend him off with his It is unclear whether this means he clubbed the dog or shot the dog Both Cooper and Degan then took cover in the According to Cooper Kevin Harris and Samuel Weaver continued walking down the road apparently not noticing the After they had passed by on the road Degan got up on one knee raised his gun and shouted Stop Marshal Harris then the weapon around at hip level and He didn't bring the weapon up to eye I saw Bill's arm going back and I knew he had been Cooper fired at Harris and Harris went Cooper then brought his weapon to bear on Samuel but did not At this point Cooper then heard two shots to his Samuel Weaver looked in the direction of the shots yelled You son of a bitch and ran toward Cooper then realized that shots were coming at him from directly ahead so he fired a three round burst at the At this point he then saw Samuel Weaver running toward the When Cooper reached Degan he placed his first two fingers on Degan carotid artery counted two or three beats and then his heart Shortly thereafter Roderick and the other three marshals joined They then all heard a large burst of gunfire from the area around the On cross examination David Nevin questioned the point of throwing rocks into the gulley asking You wanted to lure that dog out so you could shoot that dog didn't you Nevin also pointed out that in last September's testimony Cooper had claimed that he spotted Weaver after the dog had left Cooper claimed that he had gone over the events in his head and decided that Thursday's account was Nevin continued the cross examination by asking what Cooper would have done had an armed man dressed in full camouflage jumped out of the woods at him no answer was available Friday April marks continued cross examination of Notes There was no coverage of Drew Ron Phillips Senior Customer Engineer Intergraph Electronics East Evelyn Avenue VOICE Mountain View CA FAX